<normalizedToken id="97D9E296CE1A5BD97E5EE34E182AE0D6" originalValue="Army’s">Army's</normalizedToken>
long march (from June to August, 1935). They were found on or under the rocks (especially near the vegetations) on sunny slopes (Figs 
<figureCitation id="78051EAA0FA499911B338DE029F643F4" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Type localities of Gloydius lipipengi sp. nov. (red triangles) and G. swild sp. nov. (black triangles), with the collection localities of some other congeneric species." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1061.70420.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/596192" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">6</figureCitation>
